Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.63,0:04:05.68,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,{\an8}I contacted him as soon as we reached the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:09.89,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mr. Pericolo came all this way \N to collect the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:12.39,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,One of Passione's capos...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.69,0:04:15.61,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Thank you so much \N for coming all this way, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.61,0:04:20.69,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,No, no, I'm the one who insisted on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.69,0:04:22.65,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Please, no need to bow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.07,0:04:25.78,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,You must be the new member.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.78,0:04:26.49,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:29.37,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Buccellati has told me much about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.37,0:04:33.29,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Now that you've joined Passione, \N you're part of our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.29,0:04:37.29,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,You may call me Mr. Pericolo, if you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.00,0:04:39.46,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:43.63,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,You, there. \N I'm sorry for earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.63,0:04:47.60,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,My companion here \N isn't keen on being touched.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.22,0:04:49.06,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.56,0:04:50.10,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.10,0:04:51.52,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Say "Yes, {\i1}sir!"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.52,0:04:52.81,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mr. Pericolo...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.18,0:04:55.69,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,...why are you dressed as a janitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.15,0:04:59.73,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,I have my reasons. \N I'll tell you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.73,0:05:02.61,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,But more to the point, \N you do {\i1}have{\i0} it, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.61,0:05:06.45,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,The ten billion lire for the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.74,0:05:08.99,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Yes, sir. Right in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.78,0:05:11.91,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What? \N What did you just say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.91,0:05:13.00,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,He said it's right in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:14.46,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.96,0:05:17.21,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Buccellati, where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.50,0:05:19.17,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,There's nothing but urinals in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.42,0:05:26.47,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I-It was inside a urinal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.47,0:05:28.39,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I mean, that's a really safe spot, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:31.85,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Sucks for the guys \N pissing there this whole time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.97,0:05:35.98,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,I see... It's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.98,0:05:40.48,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,This necklace alone is worth at least \N seven or eight hundred million.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.48,0:05:41.65,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Buccellati...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.65,0:05:46.07,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,...I won't trouble you with telling me \N where you got this fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.07,0:05:50.74,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,The organization only cares \N that you're handing it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.74,0:05:53.08,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Wait, y-you're already \N putting it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:55.37,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,C-Could I just touch it a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.37,0:05:57.21,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Give it a good whiff?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.33,0:06:05.63,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,This fortune signifies to us that its owner \N possesses commendable intelligence and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:08.26,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Buccellati.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.26,0:06:12.10,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,As of today, you're a capo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.10,0:06:15.18,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,A-All right! \N He's a capo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.18,0:06:18.64,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Buccellati's finally a capo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.23,0:06:25.11,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,You will inherit the territory \N controlled by the late Polpo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.40,0:06:29.86,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,In addition, you'll oversee the gambling, money-lending, and smuggling at the harbor...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.86,0:06:35.08,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,...as well as all of the \N restaurants and hotels in Naples.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:40.96,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Half of the profits will go to the organization, \N and the other half will be yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.54,0:06:42.88,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,This is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.88,0:06:45.09,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,He got authority just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.09,0:06:50.30,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,With Buccellati's brains and popularity, \N he'll be rolling in dough in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.30,0:06:56.02,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,But really, the ball started rolling \N after this newbie, Giorno, joined us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.60,0:06:58.39,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,Is he some kind of good luck charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:07:00.39,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.73,0:07:04.98,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,I realize you only just \N assumed Polpo's position, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.98,0:07:09.45,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,...he was assigned to a job \N that he left unfinished.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.45,0:07:17.24,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Any unfinished business left by Polpo \N is your responsibility, Buccellati.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.24,0:07:19.25,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Is that acceptable?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.25,0:07:21.54,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Polpo left an unfinished job?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.63,0:07:25.71,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,A direct order from the boss, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.59,0:07:29.17,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The... boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.17,0:07:30.38,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,The boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.38,0:07:32.97,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,The boss no one has ever seen? {No, the other boss}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.97,0:07:35.43,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,A direct order... from {\i1}him?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.43,0:07:38.77,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Correct. \N I'll tell you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.85,0:07:44.56,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,You'll be protecting \N the boss's daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.56,0:07:46.86,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,...with your lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.86,0:07:47.82,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.73,0:07:49.69,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.69,0:07:50.74,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,The boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.61,0:07:56.37,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,The boss I'm trying to expose \N and defeat has a daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.40,0:07:53.70,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,{\an8}Did you say "daughter"? \N The boss has a daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.37,0:07:58.87,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,You'll be protecting her, \N effective immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.87,0:08:01.21,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,She's in your care, Buccellati.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.67,0:08:03.71,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,In my care?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.71,0:08:05.54,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,B-Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.04,0:08:07.38,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Could he be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.00,0:08:10.46,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No, not "he"!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.97,0:08:13.05,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,{\i1}She{\i0} must be the boss's daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.01,0:08:15.93,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,That's her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.80,0:08:19.31,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Do you mind if I use the restroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.31,0:08:21.27,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Not at all, Trish.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:27.02,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Go guard her, for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.36,0:08:29.32,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The order is already in effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.40,0:08:31.74,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Buccellati!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.28,0:08:38.16,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Her name is Trish Una. \N She's fifteen years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.16,0:08:43.21,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Of course, \N Una is her mother's last name, not the boss's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.21,0:08:47.29,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Trish hasn't met the boss \N once in her entire life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.63,0:08:53.22,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Buccellati, as you're well aware, \N no one knows the true identity of the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.22,0:08:59.56,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,But as you'd expect, even the boss has a past, \N and an especially noteworthy youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.06,0:09:08.31,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,About two months ago, \N a woman named Donatella died of illness in Calabria.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.07,0:09:16.49,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,A few days before Donatella's death, she suddenly had a search conducted {It's not specified in the Japanese WHO she had look for him. The anime leaves out the subject entirely, and the manga just says "people". -Starfish}for a man named Solido Naso. {Probably a way to improve "she suddenly had a search conducted", but neither Jules nor I have any particular ideas, and it's not particularly egregious. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:19.78,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,That man was Trish's father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.78,0:09:25.25,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,She seemingly did it so that her only daughter, \N having nowhere else to go, could find a place to call home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.25,0:09:26.37,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Unfortunately...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.37,0:09:29.34,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Naso didn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.34,0:09:34.67,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The name was just an alias \N used by the boss when he was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.67,0:09:35.51,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.09,0:09:40.22,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Be wary of anyone \N looking into the name Naso.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.22,0:09:49.23,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Anyone with any standing in Passione \N knows that attempting to look into the boss's past...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.23,0:09:52.27,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,...is tantamount to \N challenging the organization itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.27,0:09:55.61,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Word about Donatella eventually spread.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.61,0:09:59.41,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,It spread even further when \N it was confirmed that she had a daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.41,0:10:02.87,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,The boss caught wind of it, too, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.20,0:10:05.33,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,He immediately took action.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.70,0:10:09.79,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Through his usual chain of command, \N he gave me the order...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.79,0:10:13.92,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,...and placed his daughter in my custody \N soon after Donatella's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.38,0:10:17.38,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,The boss must have known it instinctively...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.93,0:10:25.93,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,He wasn't aware she existed until recently, \N but now he knows beyond a doubt that Trish is his daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.68,0:10:29.69,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Shortly after I took \N Trish into my custody...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.69,0:10:33.94,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,...we learned that someone searching for her \N had just narrowly missed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.69,0:10:41.49,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,If the boss's order had come even thirty minutes later, Trish likely would have been kidnapped, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.70,0:10:44.66,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,...murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.66,0:10:47.83,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Who is it? \N Who's after her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.83,0:10:50.33,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Traitors in the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.33,0:10:52.67,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,We don't know how many there are. {select this line, hold ctrl and hit 1 and 2 back and forth to the beat of the music -G}{Oh my god, this is fantastic. -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.67,0:10:57.21,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,They're attempting to defeat the boss \N and assume control of his drug trafficking routes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.21,0:10:58.47,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Drugs...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.80,0:11:03.89,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,They seem to be under the impression that \N Trish knows some sort of secret about the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.89,0:11:08.14,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,They want any intel \N they can get to defeat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.77,0:11:14.15,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,But Trish is just a frail little girl \N who knows nothing of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.15,0:11:15.86,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,How long will we be protecting her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.86,0:11:17.61,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,One week.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.61,0:11:20.11,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Actually, perhaps a bit less.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.11,0:11:24.83,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,You'll watch over her until the boss \N finds the traitors and disposes of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:28.66,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Leave this island immediately \N and place her in hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.66,0:11:32.83,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Only the boss and I \N know that Trish is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.83,0:11:34.08,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Mr. Pericolo...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.08,0:11:38.55,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Earlier you said the order \N was given to Polpo, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.22,0:11:40.55,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,So I can only assume...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:42.89,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Your enemies are Stand users...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.26,0:11:46.51,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,That's a safe assumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.64,0:11:51.10,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,They're most likely \N acting as a team, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.10,0:11:54.10,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,We don't know \N how many of them there are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.44,0:11:56.86,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,I don't have a Stand ability, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.86,0:11:59.61,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,This is all the help I have to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.61,0:12:02.99,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,I'll be in touch if anything comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.63,0:12:18.59,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.59,0:12:20.46,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,M-Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.46,0:12:23.72,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Yes. \N Do I have to stay... umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.51,0:12:28.06,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Will I have to stay with you \N all the time from now on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.18,0:12:31.64,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.64,0:12:34.14,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,With all six of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.14,0:12:37.27,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,We'll risk our lives to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.27,0:12:38.32,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.11,0:12:42.99,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Then would you mind \N removing your jacket?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.20,0:12:46.49,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,My jacket? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.49,0:12:48.62,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Just hurry and take it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.62,0:12:51.70,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,It's not like I want to \N see you shirtless or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.16,0:12:53.87,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,I-If that's what you want...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.54,0:12:59.88,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I don't have a handkerchief, \N so go buy me one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.88,0:13:04.47,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Also, get me some stockings \N and Givenchy Blush No. 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.47,0:13:08.05,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Make sure they're \N thigh high stockings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.05,0:13:11.85,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Get the latest issue of {\i1}Italian Vogue{\i0} \N and some mineral water, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.18,0:13:16.56,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,I'd rather die than drink water \N not from France.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.15,0:13:20.61,Main,Trish,0,0,0,,Once you've finished staring at the scenery, \N go get them all for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.32,0:13:27.16,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,Protect the boss's daughter, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.87,0:13:33.83,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,So we suddenly have a connection to \N the mysterious boss I've been searching for.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.71,0:13:36.42,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,This is worth doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.04,0:13:43.13,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,If we see this task through, Buccellati will \N earn the same level of trust the boss had in Polpo.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.13,0:13:47.09,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,But if we fail, it will mean our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.09,0:13:51.35,Thoughts,Giorno,0,0,0,,The six of us know this all too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.31,0:13:57.77,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,What's the problem? \N Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.06,0:14:00.36,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,I just wanna pet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.61,0:14:02.78,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Hey, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.03,0:14:06.99,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Quit squirming!\N  I can't read it! Jesus...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.86,0:14:14.79,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,"At nine twenty-five this morning in Naples Prison, \N Polpo shot himself in the head"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.12,0:14:19.83,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Well, damn... \N I was sure Polpo was the guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.83,0:14:22.00,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,So who is it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:27.05,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Who's the one protecting our elusive Trish?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.10,0:14:34.60,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Guess I don't have a choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.60,0:14:37.02,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,"Find them," eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.02,0:14:40.27,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,But who else is as reliable as Polpo?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.65,0:14:45.53,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Only a capo could land a gig like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.53,0:14:48.78,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,And it's gotta be someone \N with a Stand ability, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.61,0:14:53.20,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Is there anyone out there who could?
Comment: 0,0:14:58.00,0:14:58.04,Main,,0,0,0,,C
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.09,0:15:07.01,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Shopping's all done!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.92,0:15:09.72,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Coast is clear!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.72,0:15:11.39,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.39,0:15:16.18,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,If I head this way, then turn here, \N I'll end up back on this street...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.47,0:15:18.64,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,...and from there, \N I need to go the opposite way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.64,0:15:20.64,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.61,0:15:28.90,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Narancia, listen carefully...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.90,0:15:32.78,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,That list has all the food \N and other things you need to buy on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.78,0:15:35.03,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Here's the keys to the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.03,0:15:37.74,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Narancia, you can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.74,0:15:39.71,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,I know you can pull it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:45.96,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,That's not all. \N No one knows there's anyone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.96,0:15:48.92,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Not even the people in the vineyard \N who own the winery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.38,0:15:54.64,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Once you finish shopping, \N go in circles along the same path over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.14,0:15:57.47,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Throw in a few U-turns for good measure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.47,0:16:00.77,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Constantly check if anyone is following you. {"Keep a lookout for anyone following you.", suggestion comes with the caveat that it's Fugo. - Jules}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.77,0:16:07.69,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,After that, you can come back here once you switch to \N the car I arranged for you in one of the city's parking lots.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.69,0:16:11.65,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,No one else knows we're \N protecting the boss's daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.28,0:16:18.16,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,...but if someone is looking for us, \N the last thing we want is for them to be able to follow us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.16,0:16:19.45,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Do you understand? {Yellow temperance guy rolling over in his grave since this isn't spoken in English}{his name is rubber soul you fucking degenerate -J}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.45,0:16:21.12,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Someone has to go shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.12,0:16:22.62,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,It's really important.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.62,0:16:26.29,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,But we need to make absolutely sure that \N no one finds out about our hide{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.29,0:16:28.84,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,I get it, chatterbox!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:30.84,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,I got this in the bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.84,0:16:34.59,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Good, then repeat everything \N I just told you from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.59,0:16:35.22,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.43,0:16:41.48,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,Once I'm done shopping, \N I'll drive around in circles around the vineyard and{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.48,0:16:42.89,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,Oww!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:47.36,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,Wrong! Quit messing around! \N From the top!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.36,0:16:47.98,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.27,0:16:50.23,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.23,0:16:52.99,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,Drive around for a bit \N so I don't get dizzy{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.99,0:16:55.70,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,Urgh! \N What the hell is wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.70,0:16:57.49,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,Help me out here, Abbacchio!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.49,0:16:59.87,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,Tell Fugo to quit \N stabbing me with the keys!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.87,0:17:02.20,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,I'm older than him, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.29,0:17:03.62,Flashback,Fugo,0,0,0,,{\an8}Now I'm worried about sending him out \N shopping by himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.16,0:17:08.29,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Whether or not he gets stabbed \N is between the two of you. {This line still needs work imo. Can't say I have any ideas, though. - Toa}{Figure out how to phrase the last part first and work from there. - Jules}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.29,0:17:15.18,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,But even if someone does decide to follow Narancia, \N his Stand ability should put a stop to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.18,0:17:18.93,Flashback,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,That's why Buccellati ordered \N him to go shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.93,0:17:24.10,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,So basically, I just gotta make sure \N nobody follows me back here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.10,0:17:25.85,Flashback,Narancia,0,0,0,,No tagalongs!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.78,0:17:33.40,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,This is weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.78,0:17:36.28,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,It doesn't look like anyone's following me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.28,0:17:38.49,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,...but something feels off...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.49,0:17:44.25,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,I have a bad feeling about switching \N over to the car Fugo got for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.67,0:17:47.83,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.83,0:17:51.75,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Guess I gotta do this, already.{"shou ga nee naa" #2 -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.75,0:17:56.47,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Where do you think you're going? \N Huh, Narancia?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.47,0:17:57.63,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,That came from down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.64,0:18:08.02,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,So, kid, where you headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.02,0:18:13.90,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,You keep looking over your shoulder. \N Someone tailing you or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.90,0:18:17.03,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Whoa, whoa, whoa, you're freaking me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.90,0:18:16.07,Secondary,Narancia,0,0,0,,Get the fuck out of my car, asshole! {I hate that these two lines are secondary font on the bottom, but they're on screen so fast that I feel like it's hard to read this line on the top and the Formaggio line on the bottom. Definitely open to suggestions though. -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.03,0:18:19.53,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,I'm the one asking the questions here!{Ugh I do not like how the subtitles here are organized. Specifically with how Narancia's line is in secondary above. Though I kinda understand it since the alternative would be having Formaggio's FIRST line being in the secondary style and then the SECOND line it's in main style which would also annoy me but ARGH IT ANNOYS ME REGARDLESS. -Starfish}{Same. I'm not sure if I'm missing something, but it seems a little inconsistent how the lines in this conversation are arranged. Sometimes they're an8'd, other times they're greyed/secondary'd. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.53,0:18:23.16,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Don't answer a question with another question. \N It's rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.16,0:18:26.04,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Shut the fuck up! \N I said get out, dipshit!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.12,0:18:29.17,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Guess I gotta say it...{"shou ga nee naa" #3 -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.17,0:18:31.34,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,The name's Formaggio.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.34,0:18:32.92,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,I'm a member of the organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.55,0:18:36.97,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,You already heard \N Polpo died yesterday, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:46.02,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,{\an8}Yet by complete coincidence, \N you and your entire team happened to disappear all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.02,0:18:49.56,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,{\an8}That really ain't good... \N I have something important I want to discuss with you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.05,0:18:43.06,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,Oh no... This is not good...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.06,0:18:46.68,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,He shouldn't know the truth, \N but he's definitely after us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.68,0:18:49.56,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,I-Is he a Stand user?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:54.15,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Narancia, somehow I finally found you, \N but where are the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.15,0:18:56.99,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Where are Buccellati \N and the rest of your team?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.07,0:18:59.20,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,No clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.20,0:19:01.78,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I have no idea where they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.78,0:19:04.99,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Did you check the local restaurants?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.37,0:19:04.99,Secondary,Formaggio,0,0,0,,This car... {The other hated line, see line 287 -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.99,0:19:06.62,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,It's a rental, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.62,0:19:08.50,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Buccellati was the one who rented it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.87,0:19:12.00,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Why are you driving this car \N if you didn't even know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.00,0:19:13.00,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.00,0:19:17.30,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I-I always drive around in Buccellati's cars...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.30,0:19:20.30,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,I'm seventeen, \N so I can't get my own yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.30,0:19:21.84,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,That's why I'm borrowing his.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.60,0:19:25.60,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, and did you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.60,0:19:30.77,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Apparently the mortician is trying to figure out \N how the hell to cremate Polpo's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.77,0:19:34.06,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Can't figure out how to \N cram his body into the furnace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.82,0:19:39.49,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,They'll just have to chop him up \N into itty-bitty pieces, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.87,0:19:46.49,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.45,0:19:48.54,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,{\an8}Hey, you don't agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:51.29,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.29,0:19:53.50,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Where'd he go? \N There's no one here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.88,0:19:59.13,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,You really fell for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.46,0:20:01.51,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Guess you're just useless.{"shou ga nee naa" #4 -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:04.59,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Narancia, I gotta ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.59,0:20:08.31,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Why would you go into hiding \N during a capo's funeral?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.31,0:20:11.94,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\an8}Now you fucked up, asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.31,0:20:12.60,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Since following you around isn't working, \N I'm gonna make you talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.60,0:20:15.56,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,You're gonna tell me everything \N I wanna know right here and now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.56,0:20:16.98,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Motherfucker...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.98,0:20:17.73,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.57,0:20:20.69,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\i1}You motherfucker!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.69,0:20:22.20,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You're dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.75,0:20:32.87,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,What the hell is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.87,0:20:34.42,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Aerosmith!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:37.29,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,So he's a Stand user!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.29,0:20:39.09,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Little Feat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.30,0:20:45.68,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.68,0:20:48.51,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Look how much you made me bleed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.51,0:20:50.56,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Fuck you! Fuck you! Fuck you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.56,0:20:52.68,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You're dead! You're dead! You're dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.48,0:20:57.69,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Th-This is looking dicey...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.90,0:21:00.98,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You're dead! You're dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.90,0:21:03.40,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Th-This guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.40,0:21:05.49,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You're dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.53,0:21:09.33,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Sh-Shit! He's out of his fucking mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.33,0:21:11.50,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,He's going berserk \N and shooting anything in sight!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.50,0:21:15.08,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,And I'm stuck in this cramped car \N with nowhere to run!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.08,0:21:17.54,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,That's the diciest part of all of this! {Suggesting to omit the second "of". - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.71,0:21:21.05,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,A-A bomb?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.05,0:21:23.38,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Light him up, Aerosmith!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.68,0:21:27.84,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,How do you like that? \N And that?! And that?! And that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.84,0:21:29.30,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,You dead yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.30,0:21:32.47,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Oww! Fuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.47,0:21:33.48,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Did I do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.18,0:21:35.85,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,H-He's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.27,0:21:38.23,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\pos(870,1045)}Did the blast blow him away?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.23,0:21:41.36,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\pos(870,1045)}But wait... \N There's no body parts inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.36,0:21:43.74,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Wh-Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.44,0:21:48.32,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Guess he's clueless...{"shou ga nee naa" #5 -Starfish} \N I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.16,0:21:51.45,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,I can shrink myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.45,0:21:54.08,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,That's my ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.83,0:22:00.54,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,{\pos(1300,1055)}Little Feat... Everyone always \N tells me my ability is totally useless...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.92,0:22:05.72,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,The way I see it, anything can be useful \N with the right mindset.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.72,0:22:07.47,Thoughts,Formaggio,0,0,0,,That's how abilities work.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.47,0:22:10.55,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\pos(870,1045)}What the hell? \N I can't find him anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.55,0:22:13.60,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\pos(900,1045)}This is weird! \N Damn, where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.60,0:22:14.89,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Is he here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.39,0:22:18.69,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,He disappeared as fast as \N he showed up in the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.69,0:22:21.31,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Well, good luck looking for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.31,0:22:25.44,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,I'm just gonna wait here \N and buy myself some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.69,0:22:22.27,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\an8}Where the hell did he come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.27,0:22:25.44,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\an8}He's gotta be hiding somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.16,0:22:30.70,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,A woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.70,0:22:34.04,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,This fucker bought stuff for a woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.04,0:22:38.42,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Stockings and blush... \N And it's the good shit, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.42,0:22:40.08,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Who's he shopping for?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.08,0:22:43.75,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Is it for his mom or older sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.75,0:22:47.12,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,No... Chicks are super picky \N about that stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.12,0:22:49.55,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,...so they only buy fashion and \N makeup stuff themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.55,0:22:52.55,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,{\pos(990,1045)}The only kind of chick who'd \N have a guy buy shit like this for them...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.55,0:22:56.43,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,...is one who can't leave \N wherever they're staying! {Line reads kinda wonk imo but we don't got anything. - Toa}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.68,0:22:58.94,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,This is starting to get juicy...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.94,0:23:02.02,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Looks like my gut feeling was right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.40,0:23:04.15,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,It's them! It's gotta be!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.15,0:23:08.32,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Buccellati was ordered to \N protect the boss's daughter!
Comment: 0,0:23:08.32,0:23:09.58,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,Now that I know this...{Once again I split this line to avoid the credits WITHOUT having to resort to an8-ing. -Starfish}
Comment: 0,0:23:09.58,0:23:13.28,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,{\an8}...I'm gonna get Narancia \N to show me where they're hiding.{Once again I split this line to avoid the credits WITHOUT having to resort to an8-ing. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.32,0:23:13.28,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,{\an8}Now that I know this, I'm gonna get Narancia \N to show me where they're hiding.{Had to \an8 this line after all ;-; -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.28,0:23:18.00,Main,Formaggio,0,0,0,,My ability should start \N taking effect any second now...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.75,0:23:23.08,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,That motherfucker's gotta be \N around here somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.08,0:23:26.59,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,He's probably planning to \N follow me back there...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.59,0:23:27.80,Thoughts,Narancia,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.13,0:23:30.72,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,{\an8}I'll find him and kill him first!
